04/05/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- Police used tear gas Saturday (May 3rd) to disperse a crowd of young people in Athens who demonstrated to support the legalisation of marijuana for medical purposes.
Authorities say clashes began near a students' campus and lasted for about three hours.
The crowd burned tyres and blocked traffic on a busy road near the campus.
There were no reports of arrests or injuries.
The demonstration took place in the Agriculture Faculty of the Athens University.
(Makfax, MIA, AP - 03/05/08)
